{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease a ceramic pie dish (25 cm) and set aside.","Place almonds, caster sugar and 1 tablespoon of the flour into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place 80 g of the butter into mixing bowl and melt <b>1 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add eggs, milk, vanilla, baking powder, salt, flour and reserved almond mixture and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>.  Pour batter into prepared dish and arrange pear slices decoratively over the top. Dot with remaining 20 g butter, sprinkle with brown sugar and bake for 25 minutes (180°C), until golden and cooked through. Serve warm with thickened cream (optional)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g unsalted butter, softened and cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing","100 g blanched almonds","100 g caster sugar","80 g plain flour, plus an extra 1 tablespoon","2 eggs","50 g milk","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","½ tsp baking powder","1 pinch salt","2 ripe pears, peeled, cored and cut into thin slices (5 mm - see Tip)","brown sugar, for sprinkling","thickened cream, to serve (optional)"]}],"id":"r256198","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-v1yrwD4hiAM\/XZWe4ElzzqI\/AAAAAAAAe7I\/Xqy-hS2d520YYnDdBM3v7N9bWbhnBKezwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_jSopIfVCm1TET4d9.png","title":"Almond and pear tart","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.4 g","fat":"24.4 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"29.7 g","calories":"1543.4 kJ \/ 367.5 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, ceramic pie dish (25cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the pears with apples or apricots in this recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","8 portions"]}